The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Zoysa rested

Colombo: Marvan Atapattu will lead full-strength Sri Lankan squads in the upcoming one-day and Test series against Bangladesh at home, it was announced Tuesday. 

The selectors named allrounder Thilan Samaraweera and opener Avishka Gunawardene in the one-day squad. They replace pacer Nuwan Zoysa and Lasith Malinga. We are resting Zoysa for both the one-day and Test series, while Malinga will play only in Tests, said chairman of selectors Lalith Kaluperuma. 

ODI SQUAD 

Maravan Atapattu, Sanath Jayasuriya, Upul Tharanga, Kumar Sangakkara, Mahela Jayawardene, Russel Arnold, Tillekeratne Dilshan, Chaminda Vaas, Upul Chandana, Farveez Maharoof, Muttiah Muralidharan, Avishka Gunawardene, Dilhara Fernando, Dilhara Lokuhettige, Thilan Samaraweera. 

TEST SQUAD 

Maravan Atapattu, Sanath Jayasuriya, Kumar Sangakkara, Mahela Jayawardene, Thilan Samaraweera, Tillekeratne Dilshan, Chaminda Vaas, Farveez Maharoof, Rangana Herath, Muttiah Muralidharan, Lasith Malinga, Russel Arnold, Gayan Wijekoon, Dilhara Fernando, Shantha Kalavithigoda. (AFP) 




